headline: NBA Legend Shaq Abandoned A $40 Million Reebok Shoe Deal After A Lady Confronted Him Over High Price Tag: 'Ma'am, I Don't Make The Prices'
summary: Shaquille O'Neal isn't just known for his dominance on the basketball court or his $500 million net worth as a savvy business owner. He also stands by his principles, even when it means leaving millions on the table. In 1998, Shaq made what he calls his "best business decision" – a move that set him apart as more than just an athlete chasing profits. headline: The ‘Woke Inc’ campaigners preparing to fight Trump’s America
summary: Donald Trump had a warning for corporate America’s do-gooders. The president-elect said he had compiled a list of “woke companies” in February and threatened to publish it “for the world to see”.

headline: Could the Rise of E-Commerce Sales at Walmart and Costco Spell Trouble for Amazon?
summary: Amazon (NASDAQ: AMZN) has an unmatched e-commerce presence and a lead so wide it would be impossible for any competitor to get even close to it in the near future.  Does this spell trouble for Amazon?  What many customers are discovering is that combining in-store and online shopping -- even for the same purchase -- often makes the most sense.
